## 🔹 ROW_NUMBER()

- Assigns unique ranking to each row  
- Used with `OVER (ORDER BY salary DESC)`  
- Commonly used for Top N queries  

---

## 🔹 CTE (WITH Clause)

- Temporary result set  
- Improves query readability  
- Makes complex queries easier to manage  
- Helps in debugging  

---

## 🔹 ANY Operator

- Used in multi-row subqueries  
- `> ANY` means greater than the minimum value returned by the subquery  
- Useful for comparison against multiple values  

---

## 🔹 Correlated Subquery

- Inner query depends on outer query  
- Executes once per outer row  
- Commonly used for group-based comparisons (e.g., highest salary per department)  

---

## 🔹 Stored Procedure

- Used to modify data (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE)  
- Contains reusable business logic  
- Improves performance and code organization  

---

## 🔹 Function (UDF – User Defined Function)

- Used inside `SELECT` statements  
- Returns calculated value  
- Reusable and simplifies complex calculations  

